<Link id="l00021" /><CodeLine lineNumber="21"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// RewriteRope is a &quot;strong&quot; string class, designed to make insertions and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00022" /><CodeLine lineNumber="22"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// deletions in the middle of the string nearly constant time (really, they are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="23"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// O(log N), but with a very low constant factor).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="24"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="25"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The implementation of this datastructure is a conceptual linear sequence of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// RopePiece elements.  Each RopePiece represents a view on a separately</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// allocated and reference counted string.  This means that splitting a very</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// long string can be done in constant time by splitting a RopePiece that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// references the whole string into two rope pieces that reference each half.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Once split, another string can be inserted in between the two halves by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// inserting a RopePiece in between the two others.  All of this is very</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// inexpensive: it takes time proportional to the number of RopePieces, not the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// length of the strings they represent.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// While a linear sequences of RopePieces is the conceptual model, the actual</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// implementation captures them in an adapted B+ Tree.  Using a B+ tree (which</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// is a tree that keeps the values in the leaves and has where each node</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// contains a reasonable number of pointers to children/values) allows us to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// maintain efficient operation when the RewriteRope contains a &#42;huge&#42; number</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// of RopePieces.  The basic idea of the B+ Tree is that it allows us to find</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the RopePiece corresponding to some offset very efficiently, and it</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// automatically balances itself on insertions of RopePieces (which can happen</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// for both insertions and erases of string ranges).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The one wrinkle on the theory is that we don&#39;t attempt to keep the tree</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// properly balanced when erases happen.  Erases of string data can both insert</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// new RopePieces (e.g. when the middle of some other rope piece is deleted,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// which results in two rope pieces, which is just like an insert) or it can</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// reduce the number of RopePieces maintained by the B+Tree.  In the case when</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the number of RopePieces is reduced, we don&#39;t attempt to maintain the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="51"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// standard &#39;invariant&#39; that each node in the tree contains at least</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00052" /><CodeLine lineNumber="52"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#39;WidthFactor&#39; children/values.  For our use cases, this doesn&#39;t seem to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="53"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// matter.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="54"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00055" /><CodeLine lineNumber="55"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The implementation below is primarily implemented in terms of three classes:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00056" /><CodeLine lineNumber="56"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   RopePieceBTreeNode - Common base class for:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00057" /><CodeLine lineNumber="57"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00058" /><CodeLine lineNumber="58"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     RopePieceBTreeLeaf - Directly manages up to &#39;2&#42;WidthFactor&#39; RopePiece</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00059" /><CodeLine lineNumber="59"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///          nodes.  This directly represents a chunk of the string with those</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00060" /><CodeLine lineNumber="60"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///          RopePieces concatenated.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00061" /><CodeLine lineNumber="61"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     RopePieceBTreeInterior - An interior node in the B+ Tree, which manages</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00062" /><CodeLine lineNumber="62"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///          up to &#39;2&#42;WidthFactor&#39; other nodes in the tree.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00063" /><CodeLine lineNumber="63"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00064" /><CodeLine lineNumber="64" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/anonymous-rewriterope-cpp-"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">namespace </span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00065" /><CodeLine lineNumber="65"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00066" /><CodeLine lineNumber="66"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// RopePieceBTreeNode Class</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="68"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00761" /><CodeLine lineNumber="761"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// MakeRopeString - This copies the specified byte range into some instance of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// RopeRefCountString, and return a RopePiece that represents it.  This uses</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the AllocBuffer object to aggregate requests for small strings into one</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// allocation instead of doing tons of tiny allocations.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/ropepiece">RopePiece</a> RewriteRope::MakeRopeString(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">char</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#42;Start, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">char</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#42;End) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Len = End - Start;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00767" /><CodeLine lineNumber="767"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/amdgpu/silowercontrolflow-cpp/#a4868c5d81c5ccc98c47aeab6244346a0">assert</a>(Len &amp;&amp; </span><span class="doxyHighlightStringLiteral">&quot;Zero length RopePiece is invalid!&quot;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00768" /><CodeLine lineNumber="768"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00769" /><CodeLine lineNumber="769"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If we have space for this string in the current alloc buffer, use it.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00770" /><CodeLine lineNumber="770"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (AllocOffs + Len &lt;= AllocChunkSize) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00771" /><CodeLine lineNumber="771"><span class="doxyHighlight">    memcpy(AllocBuffer-&gt;Data + AllocOffs, Start, Len);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00772" /><CodeLine lineNumber="772"><span class="doxyHighlight">    AllocOffs += Len;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00773" /><CodeLine lineNumber="773"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/ropepiece">RopePiece</a>(AllocBuffer, AllocOffs - Len, AllocOffs);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00774" /><CodeLine lineNumber="774"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00775" /><CodeLine lineNumber="775"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00776" /><CodeLine lineNumber="776"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If we don&#39;t have enough room because this specific allocation is huge,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00777" /><CodeLine lineNumber="777"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// just allocate a new rope piece for it alone.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00778" /><CodeLine lineNumber="778"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Len &gt; AllocChunkSize) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00779" /><CodeLine lineNumber="779"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/inlineorder-cpp/#a7ee6f0cb51c3b9056199e9a0001fe8c3a6f6cb72d544962fa333e2e34ce64f719">Size</a> = End - Start + </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">sizeof</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/roperefcountstring">RopeRefCountString</a>) - 1;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00780" /><CodeLine lineNumber="780"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#42;Res = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">reinterpret&#95;cast&lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/roperefcountstring">RopeRefCountString</a> &#42;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">&gt;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">new</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">char</span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#91;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/inlineorder-cpp/#a7ee6f0cb51c3b9056199e9a0001fe8c3a6f6cb72d544962fa333e2e34ce64f719">Size</a>&#93;);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00781" /><CodeLine lineNumber="781"><span class="doxyHighlight">    Res-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/roperefcountstring/#a97cb45eb475a758d611227eef10e619c">RefCount</a> = 0;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00782" /><CodeLine lineNumber="782"><span class="doxyHighlight">    memcpy(Res-&gt;Data, Start, End - Start);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00784" /><CodeLine lineNumber="784"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00785" /><CodeLine lineNumber="785"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00786" /><CodeLine lineNumber="786"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Otherwise, this was a small request but we just don&#39;t have space for it</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00787" /><CodeLine lineNumber="787"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Make a new chunk and share it with later allocations.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00788" /><CodeLine lineNumber="788"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00789" /><CodeLine lineNumber="789"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> AllocSize = <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/amdhsakerneldescriptor-h/#a276e8a32e0bbf024aadd9420b8f2d3b3">offsetof</a>(RopeRefCountString, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#aa20539e89704d20b98b97e9c3feac934">Data</a>) + AllocChunkSize;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00790" /><CodeLine lineNumber="790"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#42;Res = </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">reinterpret&#95;cast&lt;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">RopeRefCountString &#42;</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">&gt;</span><span class="doxyHighlight">(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">new</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">char</span><span class="doxyHighlight">&#91;AllocSize&#93;);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00791" /><CodeLine lineNumber="791"><span class="doxyHighlight">  Res-&gt;RefCount = 0;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00794" /><CodeLine lineNumber="794"><span class="doxyHighlight">  AllocOffs = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/omp/#a16d7c5f77008a84ae20bf4a5c41e51f0ae88b4464fe326a51e6e6dfae28dd536d">Len</a>;</span></CodeLine>
